<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!--
    Demo Task 09 - Initial intake review for Pending case (Closed / Review)
    ====================================================================

    Synthetic seed record for the case-management POC scoped application.
    This file (with sibling task 10) was added in response to the QA
    Checkpoint 10 MINOR finding documenting that AAP Section 0.3.1's
    LITERAL requirement -

        "at least one open and one closed task per demo case in
         `In Progress` or `Pending` state, to exercise the
         'all-tasks-closed' gate"

    - was satisfied for case 03 (which carries one Open + one Closed
    task), but NOT for case 04 (Pending) and case 08 (In Progress),
    each of which carried only non-Closed tasks. The original 8-task
    fixture (tasks 01 through 08) demonstrated the resolve-blocker /
    resolve-success gates via cases 03/05 (General Inquiry) and 08/09
    (Complaint), but cases 04 and 08 lacked a "completed historical
    Closed task" exemplar that proves the resolve-gate's GlideRecord
    query correctly filters Closed children OUT of the non-Closed
    child count.

    THIS task (Demo Task 09) closes that gap for case 04 by
    contributing a Closed Review task whose presence in the seed
    dataset demonstrates that the validate_resolved_transition
    subflow (../../flows/sub_flows/validate_resolved_transition.xml)
    correctly EXCLUDES Closed children when computing the non-Closed
    child count. Sibling task 10 closes the equivalent gap for
    case 08.

    Updated 10-task fixture matrix (tasks 09-10 added per QA
    Checkpoint 10 MINOR finding remediation):

        Task 01 - Open        / Investigation / parent case 03 (In Progress GI)
        Task 02 - Closed      / Review        / parent case 03 (In Progress GI)
        Task 03 - Open        / Follow-up     / parent case 04 (Pending GI)
        Task 04 - Closed      / Review        / parent case 05 (Resolved GI)
        Task 05 - Closed      / Other         / parent case 05 (Resolved GI)
        Task 06 - In Progress / Investigation / parent case 08 (In Progress Complaint)
        Task 07 - Open        / Investigation / parent case 08 (In Progress Complaint)
        Task 08 - Closed      / Review        / parent case 09 (Resolved Complaint)
        Task 09 - Closed      / Review        / parent case 04 (Pending GI)        ## THIS FILE
        Task 10 - Closed      / Review        / parent case 08 (In Progress Complaint)

    AAP literal-compliance state (per AAP Section 0.3.1):
      * Case 03 (In Progress GI):       Open (task 01) + Closed (task 02)             ✓
      * Case 04 (Pending GI):           Open (task 03) + Closed (task 09 - THIS)      ✓ NEW
      * Case 08 (In Progress Complaint): Open (task 07) + Closed (task 10)            ✓ NEW
        (also In Progress task 06; the AAP requires "at least one open
         and one closed", which is satisfied; the In Progress task 06
         is supplemental coverage of the third Choice value.)

    Lifecycle position - WHY Closed / Review / parent General Inquiry
    case Pending is meaningful:
      Per AAP Section 0.5.5 the canonical Pending case semantics:
      a Pending case is one where the agent has placed the case on
      hold awaiting external input (case 04's pending_reason =
      "Awaiting Info"). During the Pending interval the agent's
      historical activity remains visible as Closed child tasks -
      tasks the agent has already completed before the case was
      placed on hold. THIS task models that historical activity:
      the agent's initial intake review (a typical first-stage
      activity for any new case) was completed BEFORE the case
      was placed in Pending status awaiting external info.

      The Review task type semantically captures the agent's
      review-and-validation step (per AAP Section 0.5.7's case_task
      type Choice list: Investigation, Review, Follow-up, Other).
      Pairing Review with Closed status models a completed initial
      review - the case has been reviewed, and the agent's open
      action (per task 03, the "Follow up with requester" Open
      Follow-up task) is the OUTBOUND clarifying contact that
      depends on the COMPLETED initial review.

      The negative due_date offset (-2 days, i.e., 2026-04-29
      relative to the build-environment baseline of 2026-05-01)
      reflects that the review occurred in the past. The
      my_overdue_tasks report (../../reports/x_casemgmt_my_overdue_
      tasks.xml) correctly EXCLUDES this task because its filter
      requires status != Closed; this Closed task is excluded
      regardless of its due_date.

    Role / cross-dependency context (per AAP Section 0.5.2):

      This task DEPENDS ON (loaded BEFORE this record):
        - The scoped application records under ../../app/
        - The case_task table at ../../tables/x_casemgmt_case_task.xml
        - All dictionary entries for case_task fields under
            ../../dictionary/x_casemgmt_case_task_*.xml
        - The choice records at ../../choices/sys_choice_case_task_type.xml
            (registers "Review") and ../../choices/sys_choice_case_task_status.xml
            (registers "Closed")
        - The auto-numbering record at ../../numbers/sys_number_x_casemgmt_case_task.xml
        - The role records under ../../roles/ and ACL records under ../../acl/
        - ../users/sys_user_x_casemgmt_demo_agent.xml (referenced by <assigned_to>;
            resolved by user_name lookup)
        - ../cases/x_casemgmt_case_demo_04.xml (referenced by <case>;
            resolved by number lookup)

      This task IS REFERENCED BY (loaded AFTER this record):
        - The validate_resolved_transition subflow at
            ../../flows/sub_flows/validate_resolved_transition.xml
            EXCLUDES this task from its non-Closed child count (the
            subflow's query filters on status != Closed, and this
            task IS Closed). This task's presence demonstrates the
            subflow's correct exclusion behavior.
        - The Agent Workspace dashboard's "My Overdue Tasks" widget
            EXCLUDES this task (the report's status != Closed filter
            removes Closed tasks from the overdue list regardless
            of due_date).

    Implementation notes:
      1. Synthetic data only; no PII. Subject text is generic
         ("Initial intake review for Pending case") and contains
         no real names, real email addresses, or real organization
         references.
      2. Sys-id-literal validation: only ONE <sys_id> element
         appears below (the task's own primary key). NO sys_id
         literals appear in any cross-reference field. The
         <case>, <assigned_to>, <sys_package>, <sys_scope>
         elements all use display_value query-by-key resolution
         (per AAP Section 0.5.2).
      3. Element ordering is strictly alphabetical within the
         <x_casemgmt_case_task> element: assigned_to, case,
         due_date, status, subject, sys_class_name, sys_created_by,
         sys_id, sys_package, sys_scope, sys_update_name, type.
         This matches every peer task file.
      4. Sys_id derivation: deterministic 32-character lowercase
         hex value computed as MD5(subject):
             MD5("Demo task 09: Initial intake review for Pending case")
             = 29660c234fc925b7e37a57c0e0aa9406
         This matches the convention used by every peer task
         (e.g., task 02 = MD5("Demo task 02: Initial review
         complete") = 949c29a044d9fd7468ddf410173ef684).
      5. Audit fields: <sys_created_by>admin</sys_created_by> for
         consistent repeatable timestamps across re-imports. The
         <sys_recorded_at> field is captured in the parent Update
         Set <sys_update_xml> envelope, not in the inner record.
      6. Choice value spelling: "Closed" (Title Case "C") and
         "Review" (Title Case "R") match the registered choice
         values verbatim.
      7. Audit-trail consideration: this task's parent case
         (CASE0000004) is currently in Pending status. The fact
         that a Closed Review task exists for this case correctly
         models a real-world workflow: an agent typically performs
         an INITIAL REVIEW of a new case (this Closed task) BEFORE
         placing the case in Pending awaiting external input
         (case 04's Pending pending_reason="Awaiting Info").
-->
<record_update table="x_casemgmt_case_task">
    <x_casemgmt_case_task action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE">
        <assigned_to display_value="x_casemgmt_demo_agent">x_casemgmt_demo_agent</assigned_to>
        <case display_value="CASE0000004">CASE0000004</case>
        <due_date>2026-04-29</due_date>
        <status>Closed</status>
        <subject>Demo task 09: Initial intake review for Pending case</subject>
        <sys_class_name>x_casemgmt_case_task</sys_class_name>
        <sys_created_by>admin</sys_created_by>
        <sys_id>29660c234fc925b7e37a57c0e0aa9406</sys_id>
        <sys_package display_value="Case Management" source="x_casemgmt">x_casemgmt</sys_package>
        <sys_scope display_value="Case Management">x_casemgmt</sys_scope>
        <sys_update_name>x_casemgmt_case_task_demo_09</sys_update_name>
        <type>Review</type>
    </x_casemgmt_case_task>
</record_update>
